00:41:21,600 --> 00:41:27,520
 Well, contrary to popular belief, he doesn't show up with a ruler in hand.

708
00:41:27,520 --> 00:41:35,080
 Growing up, my mom, she had a paint switch and labeled on it was Kylan's attitude adjuster.

709
00:41:35,080 --> 00:41:37,600
 God does not do that for Adam.

710
00:41:37,600 --> 00:41:40,080
 Adam does not have an attitude adjuster.

711
00:41:40,080 --> 00:41:41,080
 God doesn't show up.

712
00:41:41,080 --> 00:41:42,080
 He doesn't condemn him.

713
00:41:42,080 --> 00:41:43,080
 He doesn't rebuke him.

714
00:41:43,080 --> 00:41:44,280
 He does not in any way execute him.

715
00:41:44,280 --> 00:41:47,800
 He does nothing that we often think God has come to do.

716
00:41:47,800 --> 00:41:51,480
 Instead, what does he do?

717
00:41:51,480 --> 00:42:02,600
 He just shows up for their daily walk and yet where Adam and Eve, they're hiding.

718
00:42:02,600 --> 00:42:04,760
 Why are they hiding?

719
00:42:04,760 --> 00:42:05,760
 Hear me on this.

720
00:42:05,760 --> 00:42:06,760
 This is really important.

721
00:42:06,760 --> 00:42:15,320
 They are hiding because for the righteous, the presence of God is delightful, but for

722
00:42:15,320 --> 00:42:18,800
 the wicked, the presence of God is dreadful.

723
00:42:18,800 --> 00:42:20,880
 They are filled with a fear.

724
00:42:20,880 --> 00:42:22,120
 They know they are wicked.

725
00:42:22,120 --> 00:42:23,520
 They are not as they should be.

726
00:42:23,520 --> 00:42:29,240
 They have been disobedient and as a result, they are to be despised above all men.

727
00:42:29,240 --> 00:42:32,720
 And yet God, he didn't pull them out by the hair.

728
00:42:32,720 --> 00:42:33,720
 Found you.

729
00:42:33,720 --> 00:42:34,720
 Guess what?

730
00:42:34,720 --> 00:42:35,720
 It's time to take your licking.

731
00:42:35,720 --> 00:42:38,360
 Like that's not what he does.

732
00:42:38,360 --> 00:42:40,320
 I love it.

733
00:42:40,320 --> 00:42:42,720
 He just starts asking questions.

734
00:42:42,720 --> 00:42:44,480
 Why does he ask questions?

735
00:42:44,480 --> 00:42:46,760
 Is it because he's not omniscient and he doesn't know what they did?

736
00:42:46,760 --> 00:42:47,760
 He doesn't know what happened.

737
00:42:47,760 --> 00:42:48,960
 He doesn't know what he's supposed to do.

738
00:42:48,960 --> 00:42:49,960
 No.

739
00:42:49,960 --> 00:42:50,960
 He is all knowing.

740
00:42:50,960 --> 00:42:55,240
 He knows exactly what to do in this moment.

741
00:42:55,240 --> 00:43:01,960
 He does what parents do whenever they catch their kid doing something they shouldn't do.

742
00:43:01,960 --> 00:43:06,200
 Seize their guilty and then just ask them, "Hey, what happened?"

743
00:43:06,200 --> 00:43:07,760
 He's trying to maintain relationship.

744
00:43:07,760 --> 00:43:10,440
 Do you see it?

745
00:43:10,440 --> 00:43:17,360
 God does not show up in a way where he ignores what's happened, but he does not show up in

746
00:43:17,360 --> 00:43:20,640
 a way where he ignores what's happening to them.

747
00:43:20,640 --> 00:43:22,520
 That's big.

748
00:43:22,520 --> 00:43:27,160
 He does see the source of their shame, but he also sees the effect of it.

749
00:43:27,160 --> 00:43:30,840
 And so he takes care of his kids first.

750
00:43:30,840 --> 00:43:32,520
 He starts asking them questions.

751
00:43:32,520 --> 00:43:36,520
 Some of the questions I think he may be asking you tonight, he asked them, "Hey, where are

752
00:43:36,520 --> 00:43:39,600
 you?

753
00:43:39,600 --> 00:43:41,400
 Where are you?"

754
00:43:41,400 --> 00:43:49,520
 He wants them to know that even when they're lost, he will still seek them in their hiding.

755
00:43:49,520 --> 00:43:52,000
 He asks them, "Who told you?"

756
00:43:52,000 --> 00:43:58,520
 He wants them to know that even when you're misled, he'll speak to them what's true.

757
00:43:58,520 --> 00:44:01,040
 And he asks, "What have you done?"

758
00:44:01,040 --> 00:44:04,960
 Because he wants them to know that even when they're guilty, he'll still save them from

759
00:44:04,960 --> 00:44:06,880
 their sin.

760
00:44:06,880 --> 00:44:07,880
 Don't you see?

761
00:44:07,880 --> 00:44:08,920
 And this is big.

762
00:44:08,920 --> 00:44:12,440
 This is what Genesis 3 is about.

763
00:44:12,440 --> 00:44:21,400
 God's fundamental response to human failure, to your failure, is not condemnation.

764
00:44:21,400 --> 00:44:23,360
 It is compassion.

765
00:44:23,360 --> 00:44:24,960
 It is compassion.

766
00:44:24,960 --> 00:44:30,980
 And I wholeheartedly believe, which is why I'm taking the time to get it out of me and

767
00:44:30,980 --> 00:44:36,960
 give it over to you, that he is asking some of you the same questions tonight.

768
00:44:36,960 --> 00:44:40,140
 He's looking at you and he's asking, "Where are you?

769
00:44:40,140 --> 00:44:41,140
 Where are you?

770
00:44:41,140 --> 00:44:43,080
 You're not where you're supposed to be.

771
00:44:43,080 --> 00:44:44,120
 We're supposed to walk.

772
00:44:44,120 --> 00:44:45,800
 We're supposed to be with one another.

773
00:44:45,800 --> 00:44:47,200
 We're supposed to be in relationship.

774
00:44:47,200 --> 00:44:48,200
 Where are you?

775
00:44:48,200 --> 00:44:51,040
 You're not where you're supposed to be.

776
00:44:51,040 --> 00:44:52,920
 Who told you that?

777
00:44:52,920 --> 00:44:54,360
 Why are you listening to those lies?

778
00:44:54,360 --> 00:44:55,760
 I didn't tell you that.

779
00:44:55,760 --> 00:44:56,760
 I've told you what's true.

780
00:44:56,760 --> 00:44:58,800
 I've declared to you that you're mine.

781
00:44:58,800 --> 00:44:59,800
 You're my son.

782
00:44:59,800 --> 00:45:00,800
 You're my daughter.

783
00:45:00,800 --> 00:45:01,800
 You're safe.

784
00:45:01,800 --> 00:45:02,800
 You're secure.

785
00:45:02,800 --> 00:45:04,920
 You're sealed forever in Christ Jesus by way of the Spirit into eternal life.

786
00:45:04,920 --> 00:45:06,000
 I don't want you just now.

787
00:45:06,000 --> 00:45:07,280
 I want you always."

788
00:45:07,280 --> 00:45:10,000
 He's asking, "What have you done?

789
00:45:10,000 --> 00:45:16,280
 What have you done that I cannot clean, that I cannot fix, that I cannot solve?"

790
00:45:16,280 --> 00:45:18,720
 He's asking you tonight, "Where are you?

791
00:45:18,720 --> 00:45:19,900
 Who told you?

792
00:45:19,900 --> 00:45:22,800
 What have you done?"

793
00:45:22,800 --> 00:45:28,200
 Because I, I can be right when you have been wrong.

794
00:45:28,200 --> 00:45:34,080
 You may not take responsibility, but I can take responsibility for you.

795
00:45:34,080 --> 00:45:36,920
 Last story.

796
00:45:36,920 --> 00:45:44,920
 Just last week, as I'm sure many of you did, and so too did people from all over the globe,

797
00:45:44,920 --> 00:45:48,960
 I sat down to watch the opening ceremony of the Olympics.

798
00:45:48,960 --> 00:45:51,320
 And the event was amazing.

799
00:45:51,320 --> 00:45:57,240
 And towards the end of the time, they do what is ceremonially true of every opening ceremony

800
00:45:57,240 --> 00:45:58,240
 at the Olympics.

801
00:45:58,240 --> 00:46:00,320
 They bring in the Olympic torch.

802
00:46:00,320 --> 00:46:05,600
 I don't know if you know this about the Olympic torch, but the Olympic torch is riddled with

803
00:46:05,600 --> 00:46:06,600
 symbolism.

804
00:46:06,600 --> 00:46:12,240
 It is so very significant because that torch is not lit by just any regular old flame.

805
00:46:12,240 --> 00:46:15,840
 No one just struck a match or, you know, pulled out the flamethrower and decided to light

806
00:46:15,840 --> 00:46:16,840
 the Olympic torch.

807
00:46:16,840 --> 00:46:18,440
 Instead, it is lit with a different fire.

808
00:46:18,440 --> 00:46:21,840
 It is lit with a fire from another world.

809
00:46:21,840 --> 00:46:26,080
 It is lit with the fire from the sun.

810
00:46:26,080 --> 00:46:37,800
 And that fire is carried from Olympia, Greece, every single games, and it travels miles,

811
00:46:37,800 --> 00:46:43,640
 thousands of miles to reach its ultimate destination.

812
00:46:43,640 --> 00:46:47,160
 And so as I saw them bringing the torch in, I was thinking about this moment that I was

813
00:46:47,160 --> 00:46:49,820
 going to have with you.

814
00:46:49,820 --> 00:46:56,480
 And I couldn't help but wonder, what happens if something goes wrong?

815
00:46:56,480 --> 00:46:58,740
 It travels that far.

816
00:46:58,740 --> 00:47:00,240
 Surely it's been extinguished.

817
00:47:00,240 --> 00:47:01,560
 Surely it's been quenched.

818
00:47:01,560 --> 00:47:03,240
 Surely it's burned out at some point.

819
00:47:03,240 --> 00:47:08,080
 What happens in that event?

820
00:47:08,080 --> 00:47:12,240
 You want to know what happens?

821
00:47:12,240 --> 00:47:15,640
 There is a second flame.

822
00:47:15,640 --> 00:47:24,920
 There is a substitute that stands in the gap, that burns where the first failed to burn

823
00:47:24,920 --> 00:47:25,920
 brightest.

824
00:47:25,920 --> 00:47:32,360
 Friends, we have a second flame.

825
00:47:32,360 --> 00:47:34,820
 We have the second Adam.

826
00:47:34,820 --> 00:47:39,280
 We have gone wrong, but he has stood in the gap.

827
00:47:39,280 --> 00:47:40,960
 He has taken our place.

828
00:47:40,960 --> 00:47:46,240
 He is from another world, but he has stepped into yours that you might know him, that you

829
00:47:46,240 --> 00:47:52,000
 might trust him, that you might believe in him, and you might be saved by him.

830
00:47:52,000 --> 00:47:59,760
 Do you know this compassionate, not condemning king?

831
00:47:59,760 --> 00:48:11,640
 If you don't, he's asking, where are you, because I'm here.

832
00:48:11,640 --> 00:48:13,820
 Let me pray that you would take the invitation.

833
00:48:13,820 --> 00:48:16,520
 God, I thank you for tonight.

834
00:48:16,520 --> 00:48:22,800
 Thank you, God, for just the power of your word, the sufficiency of it.

835
00:48:22,800 --> 00:48:30,540
 I'm grateful, God, that, Lord, you've produced in me, produced in us, just this posture of

836
00:48:30,540 --> 00:48:36,120
 heart that God says, we're not playing games anymore.

837
00:48:36,120 --> 00:48:39,600
 World is filled with distraction and division.

838
00:48:39,600 --> 00:48:40,960
 This will not be a place like that.

839
00:48:40,960 --> 00:48:42,020
 We will not be distracted.

840
00:48:42,020 --> 00:48:43,020
 We will not be divided.

841
00:48:43,020 --> 00:48:44,240
 God, no.

842
00:48:44,240 --> 00:48:45,240
 We will be devoted.

843
00:48:45,240 --> 00:48:47,400
 We will be united.

844
00:48:47,400 --> 00:48:50,720
 And yet, God, as we claim that, we know there is only one name that unites.

845
00:48:50,720 --> 00:48:54,800
 There is only one name that saves, and it's yours.

846
00:48:54,800 --> 00:48:56,160
 It's Jesus.

847
00:48:56,160 --> 00:49:08,120
 Oh, God, I pray, as we said at the beginning, in an evening that matters, won't you prove

848
00:49:08,120 --> 00:49:10,480
 it to us?

849
00:49:10,480 --> 00:49:23,320
 Won't you pierce the heart that is within, pull it out, and hold it forever?

850
00:49:23,320 --> 00:49:32,120
 Christ, we thank you that you lived the life we couldn't, that you died the death we deserve,

851
00:49:32,120 --> 00:49:39,120
 and you rose forth, and you have made eternal life available to all people, if they would

852
00:49:39,120 --> 00:49:41,280
 place their faith in you.

853
00:49:41,280 --> 00:49:43,400
 We sing to you now.

854
00:49:43,400 --> 00:49:44,800
 Oh, God, do we sing.

855
00:49:44,800 --> 00:49:47,320
 It's in Christ's name, amen.

